{"word":"H1328 - בְּתוּאֵל - Bᵉthûwʼêl - beth-oo-ale' - Bethuel","slug":"H1328","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">בְּתוּאֵל</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>Bᵉthûwʼêl"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>beth-oo-ale'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Bethuel"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D1;&#x05BC;&#x05EA;&#x05D5;&#x05BC;&#x05D0;&#x05DC; - b<sup>e</sup>thu&#x0302;'e&#x0302;l</b> - <i>beth-oo-ale'</i><p/>Apparently from the same as <a href=\"#/H1326\">H1326</a> and <a href=\"#/H410\">H410</a>; <i>destroyed of God</i>; <i>Bethuel</i>, the name of a nephew of Abraham, and of a place in Palestine: - Bethuel. Compare <a href=\"#/H1329\">H1329</a>."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H1318\">H1318</a>, <a href=\"#/H1329\">H1329</a>"}]}